`IFormFile` buffers the entire request body in memory — that's why it OOMs. Instead, read the raw `multipart/form-data` stream section-by-section and write each chunk directly to disk.

**Key changes:**

1. **Disable the default form-body size limit** (defaults to ~128 MB).
2. **Read the multipart boundary from `Content-Type`**, then use `MultipartReader` to stream each section to a `FileStream`.

```csharp
// Program.cs
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities;
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size (default is ~28 MB)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpContext ctx) =>
{
    // Verify this is a multipart request
    var contentType = ctx.Request.ContentType;
    if (contentType is null || !contentType.Contains("multipart/", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected a multipart request.");

    var boundary = HeaderUtilities.RemoveQuotes(
        MediaTypeHeaderValue.Parse(contentType).Boundary).Value;

    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(boundary))
        return Results.BadRequest("Missing multipart boundary.");

    var reader  = new MultipartReader(boundary, ctx.Request.Body);
    var section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();

    while (section is not null)
    {
        // Only process sections that carry a file
        if (ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(section.ContentDisposition, out var cd)
            && cd.DispositionType.Equals("form-data")
            && !string.IsNullOrEmpty(cd.FileName.Value))
        {
            // Sanitize the file name
            var fileName = Path.GetFileName(cd.FileName.Value);
            var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", fileName);

            // Stream directly to disk — never buffered in memory
            await using var fs = new FileStream(savePath, FileMode.Create);
            await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fs);
        }

        section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete.");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();   // required for minimal-API form posts without tokens

app.Run();
```

**Why this works:**

| | `IFormFile` | `MultipartReader` |
|---|---|---|
| Memory | Entire file buffered | Only the read buffer (~80 KB) |
| 2 GB file | OOM crash | Constant memory |

**Don't forget:**

- **`DisableAntiforgery()`** — without it, minimal APIs reject form posts that lack an antiforgery token.
- **Sanitize filenames** — `Path.GetFileName()` strips directory traversal (`../../etc/shadow`).
- **`[RequestSizeLimit]` doesn't exist on minimal APIs** — use `ConfigureKestrel` as shown. If you're behind IIS/Nginx, raise their limits too (`maxAllowedContentLength` / `client_max_body_size`).
